      <akn:section eId="sec_32_1543">
        <akn:num>32-1543</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Appropriations.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1543_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>There is hereby authorized to be appropriated such sum as is necessary for the Mayor to administer the provisions of this chapter.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1543_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Mayor shall reclassify Office of Workers’ Compensation Hearing Examiners as Administrative Law Judges (“ALJs”) and raise their level of compensation.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1543_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Mayor shall develop performance measures and qualifications for the ALJs for the Office of Workers’ Compensation.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1543_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Within 2 years following April 16, 1999, the Mayor shall submit to the Council an evaluation of the District’s workers’ compensation program that shall include the following:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
